    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p><strong>Before you begin...</strong></p><p>Get all your ingredients and equipment ready</p><p>Skim through these steps, then wash your fruit and veg</p><p>Note: Equipment and pan sizes vary. Make sure you cook food thoroughly (even if it takes you a little longer than 10 min)</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Peel and finely chop (or grate) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Slice quarter of your <strong>lemon[s]</strong> into rounds</p><p>Cut the <strong>remaining lemon</strong> into wedges</p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a drizzle of <strong>olive oil</strong> over a medium-high heat</p><p>Once hot, add your <strong>fish fillet[s]</strong> and top with the <strong>lemon rounds</strong> and a pinch of <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> and cook for 2-3 min on each side or until the fish is starting to brown</p><p>Combine the <strong>chopped garlic </strong>and the juice of the <strong>remaining lemon[s] </strong>in a bowl with a large knob of <strong>butter</strong></p><p>Season with <strong>salt </strong>and <strong>pepper</strong> \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon butter</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Squeeze your pouch[es]<span class=\"text-danger\"> </span>of <strong>cooked long grain rice</strong> to separate the grains</p><p>Tear the top corner of the pouch[es] (just a little!) and <strong>microwave</strong> for 2 min or until piping hot</p><p>Tip: If you're cooking two pouches, pop them in together but increase the microwave cook time accordingly</p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Roughly chop your<strong> tomato[es]</strong></p><p>Wash your <strong>spinach</strong>, then pat it dry with kitchen paper</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the rice is piping hot, add it to a bowl with your<strong> traditional Italian</strong> <strong>pesto</strong>, <strong>chopped tomatoes</strong> and the <strong>spinach</strong></p><p>Season with <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper </strong>and give it a good mix up \u2013 this is your <strong>tomato & spinach pesto rice</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the fish is starting to brown, add the <strong>lemon butter </strong>and cook for a further 2 min or until the fish is cooked through \u2013 this is your <strong>lemon butter fish</strong></p><p>Tip: Your fish is cooked once it turns opaque and flakes easily</p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/lemon-butter-cod-with-tomato-and-spinach-pesto-brown-rice/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>lemon butter fish </strong>with the <strong>tomato & spinach pesto rice </strong>to the side</p><p>Spoon over any excess <strong>lemon butter</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
